The United States and the European Commission are committed to reducing Europe's dependency on Russian energy and accelerating the global transition to clean energy. They condemn Russia's invasion of Ukraine and express solidarity and support for Ukraine. The EU aims to achieve energy independence from Russian fossil fuels by the end of the decade through the RepowerEU initiative. Both the US and the EU are committed to meeting the goals of the Paris Agreement and achieving net zero emissions by 2050. They will establish a joint Task Force on Energy Security to address urgent issues related to energy supply and reducing dependence on fossil fuels.